Patch Set 1:

Abhi, here's a stab at that fix.

I'm getting a little crazy with all the jobs because it's taking so long to get a result from CI that I'm trying to hedge my bets.

I think the order of landing should probably be:

1. The existing import workflow job that we have
2. The patch to make the above also do image conversion
3. The wsgi async patch
4. This patch
5. Change devstack default back to wsgi mode
6. Change the glance jobs to let the tempest-integrated-storage job run as wsgi, the import-workflow job as standalone with everything enabled
7. Once my nova job lands, add that to glance gate, which will cover ceph, multistore, import

I think gmann is planning to get the tempest stuff landed soon, so maybe tomorrow before any of this can happen anyway...
